commit.message:
Improve { detection in interpolation regexes

Now, {*{{ x }}}* will always select the innermost two braces

Allow dashes in html shorthands

Such that attributes like `:data-foo="bar"` gets highlighted.

Use stricter keyword regex

Prevents awkward highlighting of custom directives like "v-for-each"

Add more permissive directive regex

Custom directives may now contain dashes and dots

Use correct syntax class for whitespace (#3)



https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/manual/html_node/elisp/Regexp-Backslash.html
Allow any whitespace in front of shorthand attributes (#2)

Improve regexes, add keywords, add preferences

One may now choose their preferred method of highlighting mustache
interpolations. Regexes have been made more lenient, and more types
of interpolations are supported.

We now pass `package-lint` and the byte compiler, as well
